\caption[Receptor Sampling]{
(a) Tangential section through the photoreceptor inner segments
in the central fovea of a macaque monkey.
The smallest center-to-center spacing is about 2.5 $\mu m$.
(b) Tangential section at a point 5 degrees peripheral the fovea.
The large cones are shown surrounded by the smaller rods.
(Image from Williams, data from Miller and Hirsch).
%The figure was taken from Williams 1986 TINS article.

